# Hyperflow — Cursor Rule

This project uses **hyperflow v${HYPERFLOW_VERSION}** for autonomous multi-agent orchestration.

**On every session:**
1. Read `.hyperflow/profile.md`, `architecture.md`, `conventions.md`, `dependencies.md`, `testing.md`, `git-workflow.md` for project context
2. Read `.hyperflow/memory/index.md` to surface relevant past learnings
3. Check `.hyperflow/tasks/` for in-progress work
4. Follow the hyperflow orchestration protocol: decompose → parallel dispatch → review → synthesize

**Workflow rules:**
- Print `⚡ [Role] description` before dispatching subagents (Composer agents)
- After each batch, persist reusable learnings into `.hyperflow/memory/` with tags
- Print a usage summary at task end (agent count, token usage by role)

**Project memory locations:**
- `.hyperflow/memory/learnings.md` — patterns, gotchas
- `.hyperflow/memory/decisions.md` — architectural decisions
- `.hyperflow/memory/pitfalls.md` — failed approaches
- `.hyperflow/memory/patterns.md` — reusable patterns
- `.hyperflow/memory/conventions.md` — project conventions
- `.hyperflow/memory/archive/` — compressed entries 30+ days old

Full protocol: https://github.com/Mohammed-Abdelhady/hyperflow

